{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform housing and immigration system to address racial inequalities",
        "additional_details": "We ask the reforms include:\r\nFund local Authorities to build more council homes to meet demand of affordable housing.\r\nIncrease Housing Benefit to cover the true cost of rent\r\nEnd deportations of migrant and asylum-seeking rough sleepers.\r\nProvide housing support for those on No recourse to public funds\r\nEnd Right to Rent and scrap Section 21 eviction notices.\r\nEnforce landlord licensing requirements to protect renters.\r\nPrioritise strategies to bring down toxic air levels in Black communities.\r\n",
        "background": "The UK housing system upholds and perpetuates structural racism that causes health and housing inequalities for Black people. It prioritises private-sector profits over affordable housing. Right to Rent legislation allows estate agents and landlords to check the migration status of renters.",
